title: File retrieval of distributedly created data fails from a local clone
body:
I ran into a funky file retrieval failure.
I'm on a compute cluster. My project contains files that have been created in dataset clones on compute nodes, and were later pushed and merged into the main analysis dataset. Here is the output of ``git annex whereis``:

```
(magma) adina@juseless in /data/project/brainpeach/memento-sss on git:master
❱ git annex whereis sub-001/meg/sub-001_task-memento_proc-sss_meg.fif 
whereis sub-001/meg/sub-001_task-memento_proc-sss_meg.fif (2 copies) 
        43d8b7cc-0a36-4b30-b275-5b1b4b3ecdb9 -- adina@cpu10:/tmp/ds
        925547b2-8ee7-4856-be15-a247e762eb56 -- adina@juseless:/data/project/brainpeach/memento-sss [here]
ok
```
``git annex fsck`` comes back ok. The file content of these files is present in the original dataset.

The problem is: File content (seemingly) can't be retrieved by clones of the dataset:

```
# clone the project somewhere (I tried /tmp, a directory next to the project, and my home)
(magma) adina@juseless in /tmp
❱ datalad clone /data/project/brainpeach/memento-sss && cd memento-sss
[INFO   ] Scanning for unlocked files (this may take some time)                                                   
install(ok): /tmp/memento-sss (dataset)

(magma) adina@juseless in /tmp/memento-sss on git:master
❱ datalad get sub-001/meg/sub-001_task-memento_proc-sss_meg.fif 
[ERROR  ]   failed to retrieve content from remote                                                                
[ERROR  ]   failed to retrieve content from remote                                                                
[ERROR  ]   failed to retrieve content from remote                                                                
[ERROR  ]   failed to retrieve content from remote                                                                
[ERROR  ]   failed to retrieve content from remote                                                                
[ERROR  ]   failed to retrieve content from remote                                                                
[ERROR  ]   failed to retrieve content from remote                                                                
[ERROR  ]   failed to retrieve content from remote                                                                
[ERROR  ]   failed to retrieve content from remote                                                                
[ERROR  ]   failed to retrieve content from remote     
[...] hundreds of lines of failure (funky UX bug it seems)
```

```
read: cp ["--reflink=always","--preserve=timestamps","/data/project/b
rainpeach/memento-sss/.git/annex/objects/gX/13/MD5E-s2145810666--6dc9f68f36918eb0d4e2522ac0a3ec5a.fif/MD5E-s2145810666
```

If I try to execute this command, I get
```
cp "--reflink=always" "--preserve=timestamps" "/data/project/brainpeach/memento-sss/.git/annex/objects/gX/13/MD5E-s2145810666--6dc9f68f36918eb0d4e2522ac0a3ec5a.fif/MD5E-s2145810666--6dc9f68f36918eb0d4e2522ac0a3ec5a.fif" ".git/annex/tmp/MD5E-s2145810666--6dc9f68f36918eb0d4e2522ac0a3ec5a.fif"
cp: unwritable '.git/annex/tmp/MD5E-s2145810666--6dc9f68f36918eb0d4e2522ac0a3ec5a.fif' (mode 0444, r--r--r--); try anyway? 
```

If I remove the file and try again I get
```
adina@juseless in /data/project/brainpeach/reproducer2 on git:master
❱ rm -rf .git/annex/tmp/MD5E-s2145810666--6dc9f68f36918eb0d4e2522ac0a3ec5a.fif          1 !
adina@juseless in /data/project/brainpeach/reproducer2 on git:master
❱ cp "--reflink=always" "--preserve=timestamps" "/data/project/brainpeach/memento-sss/.git/annex/objects/gX/13/MD5E-s2145810666--6dc9f68f36918eb0d4e2522ac0a3ec5a.fif/MD5E-s2145810666--6dc9f68f36918eb0d4e2522ac0a3ec5a.fif" ".git/annex/tmp/MD5E-s2145810666--6dc9f68f36918eb0d4e2522ac0a3ec5a.fif"
cp: failed to clone '.git/annex/tmp/MD5E-s2145810666--6dc9f68f36918eb0d4e2522ac0a3ec5a.fif' from '/data/project/brainpeach/memento-sss/.git/annex/objects/gX/13/MD5E-s2145810666--6dc9f68f36918eb0d4e2522ac0a3ec5a.fif/MD5E-s2145810666--6dc9f68f36918eb0d4e2522ac0a3ec5a.fif': Operation not supported
```

If I remove the file and retry with ``reflink=auto``, copying works:
```
❱ rm -rf .git/annex/tmp/MD5E-s2145810666--6dc9f68f36918eb0d4e2522ac0a3ec5a.fif         
adina@juseless in /data/project/brainpeach/reproducer2 on git:master
❱ cp "--reflink=auto" "--preserve=timestamps" "/data/project/brainpeach/memento-sss/.git/annex/objects/gX/13/MD5E-s2145810666--6dc9f68f36918eb0d4e2522ac0a3ec5a.fif/MD5E-s2145810666--6dc9f68f36918eb0d4e2522ac0a3ec5a.fif" ".git/annex/tmp/MD5E-s2145810666--6dc9f68f36918eb0d4e2522ac0a3ec5a.fif"
```

but ``get`` still fails. 

I'm a bit clueless, has anyone seen this before?
